  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $\\hat{R}(G)$ denote the size Ramsey number, the minimal number of edges $m$ such that there is a graph $H$ with $m$ edges that is Ramsey for $G$.\n\nIs there a function $f$ such that $f(x)/x\\to \\infty$ as $x\\to \\infty$ such that, for all large $C$, if $G$ is a graph with $n$ vertices and $e\\geq Cn$ edges then\\[\\hat{R}(G) > f(C) e?\\]",
